article.description: Trayvon Palmer had 17 points and 13 rebounds to lead Chicago State in a 137-59 rout over Division III member Illinois Tech in the season opener for both teams on Friday night.
article.headline: Chicago State routs Illinois Tech 137-59 in season opener
article.linkText: Chicago State routs Illinois Tech 137-59 in season opener
article.story: CHICAGO -- Trayvon Palmer had 17 points and 13 rebounds to lead Chicago State in a 137-59 rout over Division III member Illinois Tech in the season opener for both teams on Friday night. It was the most points scored for Chicago State since losing to Troy State 140-131 in 1995. Jawad Adekoya and Kieran Woods scored 16 points, and Elliot Cole added 16 points with five assists. The Cougars made a school-record 56 field goals, and matched a school-record with 26 steals, with Woods leading with four. Anthony Mosley scored 26 points and Jake Digiorgio had 15 points to lead the Scarlet Hawks. The Cougars opened on a 30-9 run and never trailed while building a 66-42 halftime lead. Jordan Madrid-Andrews made consecutive layups and the Cougars opened the second half on a 14-5 run. They outscored the Scarlet Hawks 71-17 in the second half.
